<TEXT>
texas gop gubernatorial nominee clayton williams called democrat 
ann richards a liar to her face thursday and former sen john 
tower said nebraska democrat jim exon has a reputation as one of 
the biggest boozers in the senate 
williams and richards were making a rare joint appearance in 
dallas tower who is from texas was in omaha to campaign on 
behalf of exons republican opponent for the senate seat former 
rep hal daub 
with less than a month to go before the nov 6 elections 
rhetoric also heated up in gubernatorial races in maine and 
michigan a supporter of gop candidate john engler michigan gov 
james blanchards tactics to hitlers maine democrat joseph 
brennan deflected criticism of pardons he gave as governor saying 
republican gov john mckernan might have needed one 
exon denied towers accusations and said he would welcome a 
senate investigation of his reputation he urged daub to renounce 
the allegations at a news conference daub declined to do so 
nebraskas other senator democrat bob kerrey called towers 
campaign activities wormlike 
tower left the senate after the 1984 elections last year 
president bush nominated him to be secretary of defense but those 
aspirations were derailed by allegations of drinking and 
womanizing exon had opposed towers nomination 
sen exon bore down on me heavily on the drinking thing when 
hes got the reputation in washington of being one of the two or 
three biggest boozers in the senate tower said on omaha radio 
station kkars program talk of the town 
were talking about reputation tower continued were 
talking about rumor specific comments that have been related to me 
by others so i would have to say that i dont have firsthand 
knowledge i would establish that because that is the fair way to 
do it 
in dallas richards and williams were on a podium at a gathering 
of the greater dallas crime commission when williams walked to 
richards side of the stage to greet supporters 
richards extended her hand but williams declined to shake it 
saying im here to call you a liar today 
thats what you are youve lied about me youve lied about 
mark white and youve lied about jim mattox im going to finish 
this deal today 
richards defeated white and mattox in a bitter democratic 
primary williams campaign has been punctuated by outspoken and 
sometimes outrageous remarks 
williams said he was angry that richards was spreading rumors in 
an attempt to link him with a federal investigation into alleged 
drug money laundering 
we think she stepped over the line it is our intention that 
ann richards is no longer able to spread her venom we want to make 
sure she is not able to destroy other peoples careers and 
reputations said campaign spoksman bill kenyon 
richards called williams comment unkind and said i think 
its important that clayton williams tell the people of texas 
exactly what kind of businessman he is 
in michigan a supporter of republican gubernatorial candidate 
john engler on tuesday said gov james blanchards tactics have 
been as effective as the third reich under hitler 
richard headlee the leader of a statewide effort to cut 
property taxes said blanchard a democrat misled voters to make 
them believe he supports property tax relief much as adolf hitler 
brainwashed the german people into supporting nazism 
englers campaign director backed away from the comment 
wednesday calling headlee a little zealous 
he was talking about the public relations machine we dont 
share dicks view on that said dan pero englers campaign 
director dick gets somewhat carried away and he used a poor 
analogy 
in maines gubernatorial race rep joseph brennan a democrat 
called republican gov john mckernan a hypocrite tuesday for 
criticizing his record on pardons as governor 
if john mckernan hadnt been lucky if the police had knocked 
on the door one night and arrested him for possession of illegal 
drugs he would have been in the exact same position of many of 
those i pardoned said brennan who was governor from 197886 
mckernan has admitted smoking marijuana in college brennan has 
said he never tried it 
mckernan has accused brennan of pardoning political friends 
