<TEXT>
a us initiative in the security council 
to condemn israel for using deadly force against palestinians ran 
aground thursday over plo demands for a tougher resolution 
the security council failed to reconcile the approach of the 
united states and britain with that of the palestine liberation 
organization and the nonaligned movement despite two days of 
intensive us lobbying and marathon negotiations wednesday night 
and thursday morning 
that put the united states at the risk of having to veto the 
plobacked resolution against israel a move that would infuriate 
the arab nations president bush has been trying so hard to 
cultivate in the gulf crisis 
we have a couple of issues still to be settled us 
ambassador thomas r pickering had said as tired representatives 
ended their meetings at 4 am thursday 
sir david hannay the british un ambassador and october 
president of the security council said on nbc radio after leaving 
a meeting thursday night with pickering 
i think if we fail to get an agreement tomorrow friday that 
would be very very unsatisfactory i think tomorrow is the time 
when we must have to have a vote i think weve reached the 
end of a long negotiatiing process we ought to be ready to make a 
decision tomorrow 
thursday afternoon president bush telephoned french president 
francois mitterand whose government has said it is willing to vote 
for the plobacked resolution condemning israel the new york times 
reported friday the times quoting administration officials said 
bush told mitterrand the alliance against iraq would be hurt if the 
united states had to veto the resolution 
us agreement to condemn israel after mondays killing of 19 
palestinian demonstrators by police in jerusalem has been seen as a 
major shift in public policy toward israel the us government 
commonly shields the jewish state from condemnation by exercising 
its veto in the council 
but consultations collapsed as compromise efforts failed no 
formal meeting was held thursday 
more consultations were expected friday but it was not known if 
a vote would take place 
the security council has debated the killings since monday but 
the 15 council members cannot agree on a common approach in a 
resolution of ondemnation that would be adopted unanimously 
without a us veto 
the united states on tuesday proposed that the council condemn 
israel for using excessive force against palestinians who stoned 
jewish worshipers at the western wall or wailing wall america 
itself drafted the resolution which it described as balanced 
the us decision to join the condemnation outraged jewish 
groups which flooded the us mission to the united nations with 
phone calls 
in contrast to a nonaligned draft the us resolution blamed 
palestinian troublemakers as well as israeli security forces it 
regretted the attack on innocent worshipers and asked the un 
secretarygeneral to send personal emissaries to investigate 
but plo envoys said the us proposal was so weak and tepid they 
would be embarrassed to transmit it to their leadership in 
tunis as a reasonable working document they objected to 
apportioning blame and the reference to innocent jewish worshpers 
and complained that the us resolution made it appear the israeli 
police were merely incompetent and illtrained 
the plo and others wanted the council itself involved in the 
situation in the occupied territories captured by israel in the 
1967 mideast war and to send its own team to recommend how to 
protect palestinians from israeli mistreatment 
the united states was reported ready to veto a draft resolution 
supported by the plo and nonaligned nations as being too harsh 
ignoring palestinian violence and opening the way to council 
involvement and un observers in the occupied territories 
the council on thursday worked on a british compromise draft 
the five permanent council members the united states britain 
china france and the soviet union want to preserve the cohesion 
and unanimity that characterized most security council resolutions 
against iraq 
but the palestinian problem has proved intractible so far us 
allies the soviet union and china support elements in the us 
draft but also were ready to vote for the nonaligned resolution 
differences centered on a un investigation of the violence 
whether it should emphasize protection of palestinians and how much 
weight its recommendations should carry 
the plo originally sought an independent investigative team 
consisting of three security council members israel rejected that 
as infringing on its sovereignty 
the plo compromised and accepted a british proposal for the 
secretarygeneral to send his own emissaries to investigate israel 
has indicated it could accept such a mission 
but the plo wants to make sure that the report makes clear 
recommendations for protection of palestinians that it is made 
directly to the security council and that the council takes action 
</TEXT>
