congress is considering a boost in benefits 
for the military reserves activated in the persian gulf buildup 
i believe that all of our military personnel in the persian 
gulf deserve a tangible expression of our support said sen john 
glenn dohio 
house and senate versions of the 1991 defense bill would provide 
an immediate housing allowance for reservists called to active duty 
to support operation desert shield a total of 33252 as of 
wednesday 
generally once members of the national guard or reserves are 
called to active duty for more than 30 days they receive the same 
pay and benefits as their active duty counterparts salary is based 
on the active duty pay scale for grade and length of service 
all of the reservists called up by president bush are on an 
initial 90day assignment 
the dependents of such a reservist are also entitled to 
medical care commissary exchange and other morale welfare and 
recreation benefits on the same basis as the dependents of any 
other active duty member said the congressional research service 
in a briefing paper 
the two major exceptions to the benefits for reserves are dental 
care and housing 
military personnel must serve at least two years of active duty 
service for dependents to receive nonemergency dental care and 
the house and senate bills do not change that policy 
the variable housing allowance based on local housing costs and 
paid to personnel who do not live in government housing requires a 
call to active duty of at least 140 days 
in senate legislation reservists called to active duty would be 
exempted from the 140day requirement to qualify for the housing 
allowance the bill also would exempt reservists from limits on 
payment of unused leave 
glenn and sen john mccain rariz members of the senate armed 
services committee are seeking to add those benefits for 
reservists called to active duty along with income tax relief and 
