before the full senate perhaps as early as friday 
the measure is almost identical to one approved a week ago by 
the panels foreign aid subcommittee the primary exception was the 
addition of 306 million to the bills economic aid accounts to 
conform to congress budget agreement with the white house 
efforts are expected later to strike from the bill the 
forgiveness of 67 billion in past military debts owed by egypt 
bush wants to erase the debt as a reward for egypts leadership in 
marshaling arab action against iraq in the persian gulf crisis 
the committee avoided a fight over the el salvador provisions 
delaying that battle for the full senate as it stands the bill 
would cut the countrys 85 million in military aid in half 
the administration wants the bill to restore all aid unless the 
rebels agree to a ceasefire within 60 days a move opponents say 
would undercut talks going on at the united nations 
