old gas refrigerators sometimes used in 
hunting cabins vacation cottages and other remote areas are being 
recalled because they have killed at least 14 people in the united 
states by carbon monoxide poisoning in the past decade 
the consumer product safety commission said it has arranged for 
consumers to receive 100 in exchange for the servel refrigerators 
which were manufactured between 1933 and 1957 
the commission said gas burners in the refrigerators can be 
fouled by dust rust or other obstructions and produce deadly 
carbon monoxide especially if the refrigerator has not been used 
for some time 
in addition to their use in recreational cabins the 
refrigerators continue to be used in remote areas where there is no 
electricity or where propane gas is a preferred energy source the 
commission said 
in ontario canada about 60 fatalities associated with the 
refrigerators have been reported in the past 20 years it said 
owners of gas refrigerators may get information on the recall at 
18007827431 
 
 
