<TEXT>
in an attempt to win back voters the leaders of 
italys communist party have decided to abandon communism in name 
and philosophy and become a more mainstream leftist party 
the leadership on wednesday backed party secretary achille 
occhettos proposal that the largest communist organization in the 
west and the secondlargest political group in italy be named 
democratic party of the left 
the final vote comes at a special party congress in january and 
occhetto commands a majority in the party 
the leaderships decision was more than a year in the making 
it was aimed at keeping pace with the changes sweeping europe 
reversing an electoral slide and ending the stigma that has kept 
the party out of national government for 43 years 
in a speech wednesday to party members occhetto modified the 
partys emblem a hammer sickle and star in the new symbol the 
emblem would be smaller and depicted beneath a tree symbolizing 
liberty strong roots and love of nature occhetto said 
a small group of hardliners burned a copy of the proposed 
symbol outside party headquarters the italian news agency agi 
reported 
in his speech occhetto criticized the communist model of rigid 
centralized economies while calling for regulation to protect the 
poor and the environment 
he appealed to the party to embrace the interests of workers 
feminists environmentalists pacifists and leftist catholics and 
called on the socialists italys no 3 party to unite to form a 
government 
the socialists have been lukewarm to occhettos proposals and 
indicated the party would still not be welcome in the noncommunist 
socialist international 
the socialists who have been coalition partners with the 
conservative christian democrats in the last decade hope to 
surpass the communists and become de facto leaders of the italian 
left 
occhetto presented the proposed name change at a meeting of his 
party leadership taking personal responsibility for the radical 
turn he said the new symbol would include the hammer and sickle to 
represent the historical function of the workers movement 
in recent elections the communists have held on to their no 2 
position but have dropped from the 34 percent of the vote received 
in 1976 when they came to the brink of power to around 27 
percent 
it has been even lower in some local elections 
still in a europe that has seen ruling communist parties 
toppled in the east and the once powerful french party reduced to 
less than 7 percent of the vote italys communists stand out as 
major votegetters 
occhetto won support for radical change at a special party 
congress in march but at the price of a split with hardline 
communists 
his plan won 66 percent of the vote with 34 percent of the 
delegates known as the no front opposed 
the party split surfaced again in august on a parliamentary vote 
on italys participation in the multinational naval task force in 
the persian gulf 
occhetto and his mainline allies abstained on the vote while the 
no front voted against 
the italian communist party was formed in 1921 in a breakway 
from the socialists it went underground during fascism played a 
major role in the resistance and briefly served in coalition 
governments after world war ii 
but it has been locked out of the central government since 1947 
although it holds many key posts in the country 
the italian communists long ago proclaimed their independence 
from moscow when an international communist front was seen as a 
threat to the west 
they have also supported italys membership in nato although 
the us government has been wary of their stand on strategic 
issues 
