chairman yasser arafat a diplomatic victory in an attempt to 
curry favor with the arabs 
egypt saudi arabia morocco and other arab states including 
kuwaits government in exile say israels occupation of gaza and 
the west bank is just as offensive as saddams invasion of kuwait 
saddam has been trying to link the withdrawal of his iraqi 
troops from kuwait with an israeli withdrawal from the occupied 
territories 
the last time the united states supported criticism of israel in 
the security council was in january 1988 when it endorsed a 
resolution urging israel to halt deportations of activists in the 
palestinian uprising 
the most dramatic instances of us condemnation of israel were 
in 1982 over the invasion of lebanon to force out the plo and 1981 
over israels destruction of an iraqi nuclear reactor 
