for insubordination and disobedience and as part of a costcutting 
effort at its mobil chemical corp subsidiary 
in testimony wednesday olson said inspectors spoke candidly 
with mobil managers but were careful in their notes and reports not 
to leave a paper trail that investigators could trace to higher 
executives 
olson said he saw environmental violations at the refineries he 
audited he used an analogy to illustrate how mobil wanted reports 
made 
lets say the speed limit is 55 and we saw a company vehicle 
go in excess of 55 he testified wed say we saw it going in 
excess of 50 
mobil has argued that selfpolicing eliminated the need for 
government oversight of plant inspections and audits 
bowman was fired after a los angeles county district attorney 
made an unannounced search of mobils oil refinery in torrance 
calif and confiscated documents detailing alleged air pollution 
violations 
after that the company ordered certain company records from the 
mobil chemical plant in bakersfield cal be brought to its 
outside lawyer bowmans staff was ordered to move the documents 
charles lindberg mobils chief inhouse lawyer said this was 
done in the belief that attorneyclient privilege would keep the 
documents confidential and out of investigators hands 
bowman says he opposed transferring the documents as unethical 
and immoral and that mobil knew an inspection of the plant was 
imminent 
</TEXT>
