<TEXT>
iranian moderates allied with president 
hashemi rafsanjanis government on thursday won nearly all seats on 
a constitutional body in elections in which many of their radical 
opponents were excluded 
the official islamic republic news agency monitored in nicosia 
said only 18 million people voted in tehran the iranian capital 
which has a population of more than 10 million 
this confirmed earlier reports from diplomatic sources in tehran 
that mondays poll was largely boycotted despite government 
exhortations urging all iranians over 15 to vote 
rafsanjani leader of irans socalled pragmatists was among 
the key members elected to the 83member assembly of experts whose 
main task is to elect the nations spiritual leader and interpret 
the constitution 
among others elected to the 15 seats contested in tehran were 
ahmad khomeini son of the late revolutionary leader ayatollah 
ruhollah khomeini mohammad reyshahri the former 
prosecutorgeneral and ayatollah ali meshkini who headed the last 
assembly 
the three are among only a handful of rafsanjanis radical 
rivals whose names were allowed on the ballot as part of the 
presidents campaign to squeeze the hardliners out of key power 
centers 
most of the radicals were prevented from running after the 
government said they had had to sit a test on their islamic 
credentials in an apparent effort by ayatollah ali khamenei the 
current spiritual leader and rafsanjani to reduce the radicals 
influence 
most of the radicals who agreed to take the examamination 
flunked 
before the 12member council of guardians decreed the new rule 
candidates for the assembly were approved by three senior clerics 
in the holy city of qom 
the conflict over the balloting has heightened tension between 
th rival factions and brought the longrunning power struggle in 
tehrans hierarchy more prominently into the open 
since the death of khomeini in june 1989 the antiwestern 
radicals have feared a purge by rafsanjani 
he is seeking to rebuild bridges with the west and attract 
investment to revive the sluggish economy devastated by the 198088 
war with iraq his opponents say close ties with the west are 
contrary to khomeinis teachings 
the radicals who constitute a majority in the 270member 
parliament have accused khamenei rafsanjanis political ally of 
colluding with him in rigging the elections 
the voting was conducted amid tight security after the radicals 
had threatened to stage protests diplomatic sources in tehran 
said but no incidents were reported 
in an apparent move to appease the radicals khamenei on 
thursday called on mosques throughout the nation to mourn the 
slaying of 19 palestinians by israeli forces in jerusalem monday 
the killings have particularly enraged the radicals who 
consider israel and the united states the greatest enemies of 
islam they have repeatedly pledged to destroy israel and 
humilate the great satan its closest ally 
the majlis or parliament wednesday called for a jihad or holy 
war to liberate the palestinian homeland 
the broadcast monitored in nicosia said rafsanjani declared 
friday a national day of mourning 
</TEXT>
