<TEXT>
a state judge today threw an ethics 
initiative off missouris nov 6 ballot ruling that several parts 
of it were unconstitutional 
cole county circuit judge james f mchenry said the measure 
wrongly dealt with too many subjects and that its ballot title was 
insufficient 
mchenry said the initiative amendment 5 is not in compliance 
with the procedural requirements of the constitution of missouri 
and it is therefore not to be printed on the ballot 
amendment 5 placed on the ballot through a petition campaign 
would create a state ethics commission and force big changes in the 
legislature including reducing the size of the 163member house to 
103 by 2003 
state attorney general william webster said he would appeal 
mchenrys ruling to the missouri supreme court 
willard reine president of missourians to protect the 
initiative process which legally challenged the measure said 
im very pleased i think the judge interpreted the law right 
the initiative process is important to have but its got to be 
done right 
