<TEXT>
ulysses started firing its 
thrusters thursday to point its main antenna toward earth and the 
shuttle that launched the probe was in fine shape after a 
17millionmile flight nasa said 
the space agency meanwhile formed a team to investigate why 
the shuttle discovery lifted off saturday with incorrect 
instructions for how it should operate some of its computer 
programs said shuttle project engineer chris fairey 
discovery landed early wednesday after sending ulysses on a 
fiveyear 186billionmile journey to study the suns poles 
the vehicle is in excellent condition said shuttle 
processing manager tip talone 
he said only 10 to 15 of discoverys heatshield tiles need to 
be replaced debris that hit the shuttle during its launch and 
landing caused 13 dings larger than one inch and about 50 
saller ones 
thats a very low number talone said every time we come 
back we seem to learn more about how to fly and land the thing 
without taking a lot of hits 
ulysses maneuvering which will end friday was designed to let 
the spacecraft communicate with controllers more quickly by using 
its highgain antenna a 54footwide dish said franklin 
odonnell a spokesman for nasas jet propulsion laboratory 
ulysses began firing its thrusters to start a complex series 
of maneuvers to turn itself around nearly 180 degrees to point the 
big dish toward earth odonnell said by phone from the pasadena 
laboratory 
the solar explorer has been communicating with its controllers 
through one of its smaller antennas limiting the rate at which 
information is transmitted he added 
the 250 million ulysses spacecraft is the centerpiece of a 750 
million joint mission by the european space agency and the national 
aeronautics and space administration 
six hours after discovery was launched saturday from cape 
canaveral fla ulysses was deployed from the shuttles cargo bay 
then three rocket stages hurled it out of earth orbit at a record 
escape speed of about 34000 mph 
ulysses was 368 million miles from earth on thursday zipping 
toward a 1992 flight past jupiter at 25372 mph odonnell said it 
will use jupiter as a gravity slingshot to become the first 
spacecraft to fly perpendicular to the plane in which the planets 
orbit the sun 
that will allow ulysses to fly over the suns south pole in 1994 
and north pole in 1995 however it will never get closer to the 
sun that it was when it was launched to study the suns poles 
ulysses doesnt need to get close to the sun only leave the plane 
of the planets 
fairey said the incorrect instructions were loaded into one of 
discoverys computers last thursday after that computer was used to 
update some of the programs on ulysses which was sitting inside 
the shuttles cargo bay at the time 
the investigators will recommend steps to prevent such an error 
from happening again he added 
the incorrect instructions were noticed and fixed by discoverys 
five astronauts about an hour after the shuttle was launched and 
never posed a danger to the shuttle or its crew even if the error 
hadnt been detected said milt heflin lead flight director at 
johnson space center in houston 
heflin had said nasa considered the problem serious because it 
went undetected before discovery was launched fairey called it 
really minor but said it did point out a minor deficiency in 
the way we code our software 
the incorrect instructions were among those that tell each of 
discoverys five computers which onboard devices they should 
operate during the shuttles flight 
talone said shuttle maintenance was proceeding smoothly so 
discovery should be ready for a oneday flight back to cape 
canaveral on monday riding piggyback on a modified jumbo jetliner 
discoverys new carbon brakes which have been tested on only 
