the wealthiest people in america would face 
higher tax rates but still collect tax cuts averaging more than 
9000 a year under a plan endorsed thursday by president bush 
the plan advanced by conservative republicans in the house 
would exclude more than half of capital gains from taxation and 
raise the 28 percent maximum income tax rate on the richest people 
to 31 percent it would reduce the top rate affecting some 
uppermiddleincome people from 33 percent to 31 percent 
the congressional budget office estimated people with incomes of 
200000 or more would realize tax cuts averaging 9097 a year 
that would represent a 62 percent reduction in their federal tax 
liabilities 
those with incomes between 100000 and 200000 would get a 44 
percent tax cut averaging 1541 a year families with income 
