negotiators last month would reduce from 33 percent to 31 percent 
the marginal tax rate on couples with taxable income between 
78400 and 162770 and single people between 47050 and 97620 
the marginal rate applies to any additional income earned 
taxable income is after deductions and exemptions have been 
subtracted 
in reducing the 33 percent rate the gop proposal also would 
eliminate a quirk in the law that allows people with the highest 
incomes to pay a 28 percent marginal rate while some 
uppermiddleincome people pay a 33 percent rate 
