other gop lawmakers to come up with a republican alternative 
budget 
he said his ranks were divided on whether to exchange a rate 
increase on the wealthy for a capital gains tax cut in line with 
bushs position but the house republican policy committee on 
wednesday included in its budget proposal a plan to raise the top 
tax rate on the wealthy to 31 percent in exchange for cutting the 
rate on capital gains to 15 percent 
phony populism is how house majority leader richard 
gephardt dmo portrays the latest gop effort 
democrats have insisted on rates of at least 20 percent on 
capital gains and 32 percent on the upper incomes in an effort to 
prevent what they call another tax break for the rich 
quite frankly the price is still too high michel said 
