administration officials sought to reassure 
friends of israel on capitol hill thursday as a senator introduced 
a resolution to disallow most of a 75 billion package of new 
weapons for saudi arabia 
we must not become the unwitting arms supplier for a new arab 
war of annihilation against israel said sen alan cranston 
dcalif 
cranston introduced a bill that would forbid president bush to 
sell advanced m1a2 tanks apache attack helicopters 
multiplelaunch rocket systems and tow 2 missile launchers to the 
saudis 
the sale of those items as well as bradley fighting vehicles 
patriot antimissile missiles tanker planes trucks and 
communications gear was proposed last month to help counter the 
threat posed by iraq whose troops are dug in along the border with 
saudi arabia following their conquest of kuwait 
at the same time administration officials briefed members of 
the house foreign affairs committee on what the united states is 
prepared to do for israel to counterbalance the saudi sale 
the administration already has said it will provide patriot 
antimissile batteries for israel and is believed ready to provide 
advanced aircraft as well officials are looking at creative 
financing to make it possible for israel to get the new equipment 
without paying for it said rep mel levine dcalif 
i would prefer not to see us go down this path with either of 
them levine said we should be pushing regional arms control 
but if the president is determined to sell these weapons to the 
saudis and the saudis are determined to have them we must also 
provide israel with items needed to maintain its qualitative 
military edge 
levine said he would withhold until next week a decision on 
whether to oppose the saudi sale 
