iraqi authorities in a further tightening of 
restrictions apparently have ruled that no american men 55 years 
and older will be allowed to depart iraqicontrolled territory the 
state department said thursday 
department spokeswoman margaret tutwiler also described as 
simply outrageous iraqi treatment of americans and foreignborn 
family members who left iraq and kuwait on wednesday aboard a 
uschartered evacuation flight 
aboard the flight were 321 persons including 270 us citizens 
and their foreignborn family members 
in a message to americans still in iraq and kuwait broadcast 
over the voice of america the state department said no more 
charter flights were scheduled 
however we will continue to assist with the travel 
arrangements for all us citizens and thir foreignborn family 
members who want to depart and are allowed to do so the 
broadcast said 
the message again urged americans to keep a low profile and 
exercise caution and concluded your release is of the utmost 
importance we will not stop our efforts to gain your freedom until 
the last american is home 
ms tutwiler said iraqi authorities interrogated and harassed 
the departing passengers both at a kuwait city hotel and at a 
checkpoint en route to the airport in basra forcing lengthy 
delays 
some evacuees said they were threatened with weapons a dozen 
people who signed up for the flight were prevented by the iraqis 
from leaving she said 
the delays forced a postponement from thursday to friday in the 
passengers arrival at raleighdurham airport in north carolina 
the passengers spent the day thursday in london 
virtually all the departing americans were women and children 
ms tutwiler said us officials have received reports that men 
over age 55 are now being prevented from leaving she said previous 
indications were that americans males of that age were exempted by 
iraqi authorities along with those under 18 
she declined to give estimates of the number of americans left 
in iraq and kuwait 
other officials said however there were somewhat more than 100 
americans on the flight most from kuwait based on department 
estimates dating back to last month that would leave perhaps 775 
to 925 in the two countries taking into account wednesdays 
departures 
about 104 are being detained and the remainder are the targets 
