<TEXT>
the task force investigating the deaths 
of five florida students is taking another look at an unsolved 
triple slaying in louisiana because of striking similiarities in 
the crimes 
the stabbing deaths in shreveport la of julie grissom her 
father and her nephew came to the attention of the gainesville task 
force early in its investigation 
investigators at first disregarded similarities because edward 
humphrey was not in shreveport at the time of the november 1989 
slayings sources told the miami herald in a story published 
thursday 
now physical evidence seems to be pointing away from humphrey 
and investigators are again looking into the grissom case the 
herald said 
humphrey a 19yearold university of florida freshman has been 
listed as a suspect in the slayings 
he was convicted wednesday of battery on an person over the age 
of 65 for the aug 30 beating of his grandmother elna hlavaty the 
beating occurred shortly after humphrey returned home to 
indialantic from gainesville two days after the last two bodies 
were found in apartments near the university 
humphrey faces up to 22 months in prison when he is sentenced 
nov 8 he also faces an unrelated attempted sexual battery case in 
indian river county and an assault charge in gainesville 
last week a shreveport detective flew to gainesville to help 
the task force 
shreveport police homicide lt gary pittman confirmed that one 
of his detectives spent several days in florida with the task 
force but he cautioned against concluding that one killer was 
responsible for all eight deaths 
right now were proceeding as if theyre not related he 
said 
authorities believe the intended victim in the shreveport 
killings was 24yearold julie grissom her father william t 
grissom and her nephew 8yearold sean also died in the nov 4 
1989 attack 
among the similarities in that case and the florida murders the 
herald said 
ms grissom was a petite brunette student at louisiana state 
university the four women killed in gainesville were petite 
brunettes between the ages of 17 and 23 and attended the university 
of florida or santa fe community college in gainesville the young 
man killed was living with one of the women 
the killer posed ms grissoms body to shock whoever found 
her the gainesville killer also posed the bodies of victims 
investigators in both states say the killer may have photographed 
the crime scenes 
in both states the killer left behind little evidence 
the shreveport killer used tape during the killings but 
removed it from the victims or took it with him the gainesville 
killer did the same thing 
both killers used liquids vinegar and household cleaner to 
destroy evidence on the victims bodies 
some of the gainesville victims were mutilated but ms grissom 
was not 
serial killing experts however say it is not uncommon for a 
killer to become increasingly brutal 
