defendants 
enrile rebecco panlilio and his wife erlinda were to have been 
arraigned friday on rebellion charges in connection with a failed 
coup attempt last december 
but judge jaime salazar noted the three defendants had filed 
petitions with the court of appeals to halt the case 
enrile and the others were indicted in february after witnesses 
claimed they saw coup leader lt col gregorio gringo honasan 
at the opposition senators home on the first day of the failed 
putsch 
enrile denies the charge the panlilios were attending a party 
at enriles home in makati on the day of the coup attempt 
chief prosecutor aurelio trampe charged the defendants were 
using stall tactics salazar also expressed frustration over the 
delays 
the case is hanging in the air he said im for speed 
what is important is the trial on the merits 
enrile was first charged with rebellion and murder but the 
latter charge was dropped he could face up to 20 years in prison 
if convicted of rebellion 
enrile defense minister under late president ferdinand marcos 
led the feb 22 1986 mutiny against marcos that triggered the 
uprising that lifted corazon aquino into the presidency 
mrs aquino fired enrile from the defense ministry in november 
1986 after a failed coup by his followers enrile ran successfully 
for the senate in 1987 and used his post there to lead opposition 
to mrs aquino 
