walgreen co said thursday it had ordered 
its drug stores nationwide to remove slap bracelets from their 
shelves while the safety of the fad jewelry is investigated 
the action was taken wednesday in response to a complaint 
tuesday that a connecticut child received a minor cut while playing 
with a bracelet said maryellen thielen spokeswoman at walgreen 
corporate headquarters in this chicago suburb 
we just want to make sure that if and when we do put them back 
on the shelves we know they are safe thielen said and while 
we are investigating we have asked them to remove them 
also thursday connecticut consumer protection officials ordered 
the recall of taiwanmade imitations of the popular toys 
the bracelet consists of a 9inch strip of metal encased in 
brightly colored cloth when the strip is slapped against the 
wrist it wraps itself around the wearers arm 
the state department of consumer protection issued the recall 
order after testing three versions of the bracelets for exposed 
sharp edges which are prohibited on most toys under the states 
child protection act 
only one version passed the tests the original slap wrap 
bracelets made by simsburybased main street toy said lois bryant 
director of the departments product safety division 
those that failed were labeled made in taiwan or lacked 
labels she said 
the slap bracelets sold by walgreen are imitations 
main street toy maintains that its bracelets made with 
stainless steel are not dangerous but that imitations are made 
from cheaper steel that will rust and snap 
when 4yearold nicole tomaso wrapped the bracelet she got at 
walgreen in wallingford conn around her wrist tuesday a piece 
of metal protruded from the toys sewn end and she cut her finger 
her father said 
the bracelet that caused the injury was an imitation slap wraps 
sell for 249 the imitations cost less usually 99 cents 
elementary school officials in pelham ny banned the wraps 
last week after becoming concerned about children cutting 
themselves 
