two japanese sailors held nearly seven years in 
north korea returned home thursday after being released by the 
communist north in an apparent bid for closer relations with japan 
isamu beniko 60 and yoshio kuriura 59 looked healthy and 
relieved as they stepped off a chartered all nippon airways 
airplane into bright sunshine at haneda airport 
in a scene televised live and nationwide beniko broke with 
customary japanese reserve and waved vigorously toward the airport 
