<TEXT>
marta de teixeira campos knew the 
price of a frozen chicken but that was yesterday it had risen 50 
percent overnight 
the rice black beans cooking oil and cheese in her cart were 
vital if her four children were to be fed so mrs campos 
reluctantly handed the chicken back to the supermarket cashier 
she and most of the 150 million other brazilians are feeling the 
bite of a resurgent inflation that makes survival a daily struggle 
wages dont go up to match prices and the public is gradually 
losing confidence in the economic shock plan decreed by 
president fernando collor de mello on mar 15 
inflation plunged from 84 percent in march to 33 percent in 
april and the poor elated by their new buying power gave collor a 
74 percent approval rating in may 
unfortunately inflation didnt go away prices rose 96 percent 
in june by august the monthly rate was up to 105 and in september 
nearly reached 13 percent 
helio jaguaribe a leading sociologist said inflation had now 
reached the level where it is biting into basic needs 
brazilians shrugged off inflation for years because 
costofliving indexing protected wages and savings the government 
had to print money to pay the bill however and that made 
inflation worse 
in june collor did away with wage indexing and said workers 
must negotiate their own pay increases 
in september he abolished rent control to encourage 
construction and rents tripled overnight a onebedroom apartment 
in the affluent south zone that rented for 500 a month last year 
now costs 1700 
people returning from winter vacations found the 800cruzeiro 
ride from home to the airport cost 1900 in the other direction 
a movie ticket has tripled in two months to 300 cruzeiros about 
340 a month of lambada dance lessons doubled to 5000 cruzeiros 
or 56 and the cost of an international telephone call has tripled 
since june to about 5 a minute 
prices of auto parts inhabit an unreal world of their own a 
volkswagen distributor charges 95 for a headlight enough to buy 
more than 26 pounds of prime beef 
newspapers are filled with announcements of price increases 
magazines offer advice on how to cope and invest money and carry 
classified ads from people who want to pool stocks of food and 
household items 
prices vary wildly a mens linen shirt costs the equivalent of 
560 at a one shop in downtown rio and a similar one goes for 80 
at another 
all prices may be going up but they rise more rapidly in some 
stores than in others in september a government price supervision 
agency said a check of 325 shops turned up 300 different prices for 
the same brand of suntan lotion 
comparison shopping has become a national pastime 
marcia sobreira evangelista a 29yearold lawyer said 
inflation forced her to atted the theater less often 
so what does she do instead i go to mall to see the prices 
when collors austerity plan froze most bank accounts barter 
became popular joao alves do brito starting out as a dentist 
traded his 1981 volkswagen beetle for dental equipment 
i was lucky said brito 32 i avoided a big hassle of 
getting cash and who knows when the manufacturer would have 
delivered the materials 
as inflation grows so does the amount of time and energy spent 
in coping with it 
sandra ippolito brunoro 34yearold manager of a sao paulo 
officelighting company says she spends three hours a day reading 
journals and newspaper business sections in an effort to keep her 
money from losing value 
you start thinking whatll be today gold dollars or 
putting it into the stock market she said its incredibly 
unproductive but what choice do you have 
computer analyst sebastiao freitas gomes 27 tries to beat the 
system by shuffling money between bank and investment accounts 
every friday afternoon gomes transfers money from his checking 
account into a shortterm overnight money market that pays 10 
percent a month 
its tricky he said because you have to get to the bank 
first thing on monday to tranfer money back into your checking 
account to cover the checks you wrote over the weekend 
brazilians have turned to credit cards as a way to delay 
payment there is no finance charge when the total balance is paid 
promptly and using a card locks in prices that prevailed at the 
time of purchase 
some merchants will not accept credit cards others follow the 
illegal but common practice of charging credit customers 45 
percent more than those who pay cash 
</TEXT>
