<TEXT>
he telephoned the first men on the moon he 
opened the door to china and in 1974 he became the only 
president to resign from office under the certainty of impeachment 
and the likelihood of conviction 
its 1990 now and richard m nixon is tanned rested ready and 
rehabilitated and nixon a threehour documentary is opening 
the season monday for the american experience series on pbs 
its a comprehensive biography of the 37th us president 
evenhanded wellresearched full of good photographs and familiar 
footage unfortunately nixon and his immediate family did not 
cooperate in the making of the film 
nixon makes fine viewing for someone born since 1969 for 
whom nixon is ancient history but it wont satisfy those who lived 
during his prime 
nixon has been a national figure since 1948 when the young 
california congressman made headlines by birddogging alger hiss 
alleged communist ties before the house unamerican activities 
committee 
nixon fails to show how his character led to the high 
crimes and misdemeanors that toppled him for concealing his 
governments ties to the june 1972 botched breakin at democratic 
offices in the watergate complex 
interviews with nixon historians and biographers cannot 
illuminate the labyrinth of nixons character as historian james 
macgregor burns has noted elsewhere nixon was not merely 
complex he was opaque 
nixon tells of a boy born to a lower middleclass family 
with an unsuccessful father and a distant dominating mother two 
brothers died at an early age richard was smart serious a gifted 
actor and debater 
whittier college duke university law school and world war ii 
service in the navy followed in 1946 nixon ousted rep jerry 
voorhis dcalif by claiming he was communistsupported 
anonymous phone calls said worse 
in 1950 he beat helen gahagan douglas for the us senate with 
an equally sleazy redbaiting campaign there is a 1979 interview 
with douglas who died the next year her revenge was the nickname 
that haunts him still tricky dick 
his next political leap nearly undid him fresh on the 1952 gop 
ticket as dwight d eisenhowers vice president he attacked 
democratic corruption and immediately was accused of having a 
secret slush fund he denied everything 
he bypassed the press in the socalled checkers speech 
televised to the nation he spoke of his children his wife pat 
and her republican cloth coat and the family dog checkers it 
saved his place on the ticket 
nixon uses footage from the checkers speech and nixons 
first televised debate with john f kennedy in the 1960 
presidential race and it shows the embittered nixon in 1962 after 
losing a bid for governor of california 
you wont have nixon to kick around any more he told 
reporters because gentlemen this is my last press 
conference six years later the new nixon won the presidency 
and inherited the divisive vietnam war 
his attempts to end the war diplomatic initiatives steppedup 
bombing and vietnamization of the ground war divided the 
nation even further 
the watergate era is the best and final hour of nixon we 
get to see the brooding still photos of nixon bunkered in the white 
house and the speech that claims the support of a great silent 
majority 
the film shows how the white house perceiving political 
opposition to the war as subversion compiled an enemies list 
used by the fbi cia and irs to attack its foes and created an 
extralegal plumbers unit to stop leaks 
and then there was the watergate breakin but for washington 
post reporters bob woodward and carl bernstein uncredited by name 
in nixon the president and his men might have gotten away 
with it 
as it was the reporters found a massive campaign of political 
spying and sabotage that led straight to the white house and 
triggered our nations greatest constitutional crisis 
there are excellent interviews with cheerful expansive former 
aides including john ehrlichman john dean and charles colson 
who did time for watergate crimes and speechwriter ray price 
nixon ultimately fails because of its ending there is the 
damaged man ascending the helicopter steps the sudden agonized 
wave the embarrassing awkward vsigns its still painful to 
witness his departure into exile 
but he didnt stay there and the film neglects to mention his 
miraculous rehabilitation as elder statesman for the republican 
party that omission only emphasizes the obvious history is not 
yet done with richard nixon 
 
elsewhere in television 
aampe ussr aampr ok the arts amp entertainment network tonight 
presents the premiere of the inside track with graham nash 
with the exhollies excrosby stills amp young collaborator 
discussing 90s issues with musical guests 
tonights guest artist is david crosby who will discuss the 
national rifle association alcoholism and substance abuse future 
guests will include mick fleetwood judy collins gregg allman 
herbie hancock and bob geldof 
