gov l douglas wilder has changed many 
things in more than two decades in politics 
he was the first black elected to the virginia senate since 
reconstruction 
he became the nations first elected black governor 
now the rising political star wants to change the national 
democratic party he is chipping away at bedrock democratic 
doctrine in a quest to redefine it in more fiscally conservative 
terms 
wilder fired a broadside at his own party that sounded almost 
reaganesque in its denunciation of tax increases 
a backroom tax deal stacked against the middle class wilder 
said of a quickly defeated federal deficitreduction package he 
criticized democratic national chairman ron brown for endorsing it 
in speeches and a recent interview the governor describes 
himself as the personification of a new mainstream style of 
politics that blends fiscal conservativism with social activism 
it helped get him elected governor made him a hot commodity for 
speaking engagements around the country and some say could help 
put him on the national democratic ticket in 1992 
and now he seems to be playing the role of outsider in a 
notsosubtle campaign to gain an inside track on 1992 
the next successful democratic presidential candidate will be 
someone who can identify with the totality of the american 
public and have shown soee degree of fiscal responsibility says 
wilder 
he says he plans to serve his full term of governor which ends 
in 1994 but others arent so sure 
wilder knows hes got one shot at national office and just 
about everything he does in the state is geared to that says 
larry sabato a university of virginia political scientist 
wilder risks alienating many of his strongest supporters by 
trying to wipe out a 14 billion state deficit solely through 
spending cuts 
civil rights and labor groups have been somewhat disenchanted 
with his performance so far he concedes 
the only special interest that i recognize is the people of 
virginia he says in defending his approach the political heat 
is likely to get worse when he discloses details of the planned 
cuts 
wilder concedes his record in richmond will be like a 
fingerprint if he seeks national office but he minimizes 
speculation that hes positioning himself for a place on the 
national party ticket 
the governor said i didnt include myself when talking about 
the type of democrat he believes can return the party to the white 
house 
still in his first six months in office he visited 11 states 
including the early presidential sweepstakes states of new 
hampshire and iowa he has injected himself on the national scene 
asking president bush to appoint an independent commission to 
