of any washington budget package that was intended to curb the huge 
deficit responded former democratic party chairman robert strauss 
i think people all over are looking for answers and 
solutions said former chairman paul kirk and they can ally 
with anyone who says something is wrong but the toughest part is 
to say what the solution is 
wilder winces when asked whether he could be compared to house 
republican whip newt gingrich who has established a record as a 
gop maverick like wilder gingrich loudly denounced higher taxes 
as a solution for federal deficits 
im not familiar with newt gingrichs politics wilder said 
one of the things i think differs is that ive shown i can work 
with people from both sides with all segments there isnt the 
schism that follows me that follows him 
former democratic party chairman charles manatt says the next 
presidential candidate must be a fiscal moderate because americans 
be they black white or brown arent going to step up in 
favor of higher taxes 
according to political scientist sabato wilder understands 
that a conservative white democrat would not be nominated by a 
party where the selection process is dominated by liberals 
but he also knows that a black conservative could not be 
opposed by liberals it wouldnt be in their constitution to be 
against that sabato concludes 
wilder has a point in suggesting that the democratic party must 
nominate a fiscal moderate or conservative next time around 
strauss says 
but it isnt just doug wilder saying it strauss said stu 
eizenstat a liberal has been saying it ive been saying it 
georgia sen sam nunn has been saying it i think were all 
singing from the same hymn book 
kirk said i dont disagree at all with what hes suggesting 
as the type of candidate the party needs its just easier said 
than done 
wilders new mainstream style follows two decades in which 
he adhered to liberal principles while climbing the ladder of 
virginia politics 
his father was a clerk at a black insurance company his mother 
cared for the eight children the family was poor enough that they 
had to stuff their shoes with newspaper 
wilder was elected to the virginia senate nearly 21 years ago 
the first black since reconstruction he promptly asked for 
replacement of the official state song noting that its lyrics 
extol plantation life under old massa 
he became one of the most influential senators in the 
legislature shepherding an array of antidiscrimination laws and 
winning a long battle to declare a holiday honoring martin luther 
king he won the lieutenant governorship in 1985 after rejecting 
the pleas of white party leaders to pull out they feared he would 
sink the ticket headed by gerald baliles he won the governorship 
in 1989 by emphasizing his prochoice stand on abortion 
wilder prizes political experience 
it would be awfully difficult for someone like jesse jackson 
to get on the ticket without some prior life in high public 
office wilder says he did not support jacksons bid for the 
democratic presidential nomination in 1984 or 1988 
a pragmatist wilder says unsuccessful democratic presidential 
candidates starting with hubert humphrey couldnt win in todays 
atmosphere of soaring budget deficits he says 
george mcgoverns positions on foreign policy and defense 
likely would be considered too soft 
walter f mondale is eminently qualified to be president 
but was perceived as too beholden to democratic party constituent 
groups 
michael dukakis didnt react aggressively to bushs negative 
advertising and probably lost the 1988 presidential election 
because of it 
wilder has said he foresees a black president in the not too 
distant future many people think he has himself in mind 
