epic takeover battles and soaring operating costs 
might sound like a formula for failure but they havent downed 
united airlines 
but the carrier is beating the flaps off its competition and 
many observers sum up uniteds success in two words pacific 
expansion 
earlier this year it became the biggest carrier across the 
pacific ocean surpassing japan air lines and northwest airlines 
uniteds success comes despite two leadership changes and four 
buyout bids in the last four years as well as an industrywide 
domestic business slump and a sharp increase in fuel prices 
parent company ual corp rejected the latest employee 
acquisition offer tuesday ending more than a year of constant 
pressure on the companys board and management 
but the stress never showed in the airlines performance 
we all suspect its been distracting but anybody who makes 
