cigarettes the report said and the soviet sale is probably only 
the beginning of an important trade with the former communist bloc 
countries it said 
the sales to the soviet union may take 3 percent to 5 percent of 
us cigarette production within two years the report predicted 
this combined with potential sales to other east european 
countries such as czechoslovakia bulgaria and formerly east 
germany means that export sales stand to more than offset the 
steadily declining domestic market it said 
the net result it added could be that us cigarette and 
tobacco leaf production may stabilize or increase even with the 
big declines in domestic cigarette consumption 
 
