<TEXT>
water is supposed to be cool clear healthy 
refreshing and if not free at least cheap 
but more and more people are paying serious money to have 
bottles of water delivered to thei homes saying they wonder about 
the safety of what flows out of the pipe or just dont like the 
taste 
lisa ehrlich for example says she pays 140 a month to have 
bottles of spring water home delivered in suburban bethesda md 
where she lives with her husband and their two children the 
ehrlichs go through a halfdozen fivegallon bottles every two 
weeks 
for our budget its a lot to pay but our water is important 
to us mrs ehrlich said it makes me nervous to drink city 
water plus it tastes great 
industry statistics show home delivery to be the fastestgrowing 
segment of a booming business outpacing water sales in restaurants 
and grocery stores as well as office deliveries 
a total of 4248 million gallons of water was delivered to 
american homes in 1989 an increase of 70 percent from the 1985 
figure of 2487 million gallons 
jane lazgin spokeswoman for the perrier group of america inc 
in greenwich conn said there are indications home delivery of 
water is more than a passing fad 
we find interest from kitchen designers who are building 
kitchens leaving space for the bottled water dispenser she said 
theres a certain novelty attached to it but its becoming more 
of a refreshment beverage choice 
the perrier group the biggest us bottled water company has 
three major domestic water brands great bear poland spring and 
arrowhead all available for home delivery its flagship perrier 
brand like other carbonated waters is not generally home 
delivered 
the average price for homedelivered water is 491 for a 
fivegallon bottle according to the international bottled water 
association the industrys trade association based in arlington 
va 
about 60 percent of bottled water buyers say theyre interested 
mainly in better taste the association said other reasons cited 
are safety and more specifically worries about chemicals in tap 
water 
the area where i live im not sure of the water supply said 
robert sims who has a fivegallon bottle of water delivered to the 
door of his onebedroom apartment in dallas every three weeks 
sims said he liked the taste of the bottled water but was 
motivated more by safety concerns 
therell be some brownish orangy color sometimes when he 
turns on the water sims said in a telephone interview ive been 
told that its absolutely safe but id rather not be drinking 
something that came out of those pipes 
federal regulations on public water systems set strict purity 
standards for dangerous chemicals and diseasecausing germs when 
the rules were tightened last year the environmental protection 
agency said the action could prevent up to 90000 waterborne 
diseases each year 
health issues however are dealt with carefully in bottled 
water advertisements and promotions 
ibwa members do not according to law make health claims 
about bottled water a statement from the association said 
however all bottled water must come from a governmentapproved 
source in addition because bottled water is a food product it 
must meet more stringent andadditional regulations than tap 
water 
critics of the industry contend that regulations are not tight 
enough to ensure that bottled water is free of contamination 
the environmental policy institute in washington issued a report 
last year concluding that there was a widespread misconception 
that the separate packaging and higher cost of bottled water 
guarantees a product substantially safer and healthier than 
ordinary tap water 
the report bottled water sparkling hype at a premium 
price urged consumers to ask for information about their normal 
water supply or have a sample tested before jumping to the 
conclusion that bottled water would be better 
mrs ehrlich said she was aware that contaminants had been found 
in some bottled waters she said her family was considering 
switching to a system that would distribute pure distilled water 
throughout the house 
who knows for sure if what youre getting is so great she 
said were trying to do the best but who knows the best might 
not be so good nowadays 
